font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: black"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Vatican_City/Projects&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: black">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:black;"><span class="mw-headline" id="WikiProjects"><i>WikiProjects</i></span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #E32636; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: #FFFFFF;opacity: 1; color: black; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<table style="width:100%; background:none">\n<tr>\n<td style="width:50px">\n<div class="floatright"><img alt="WikiProjects" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/00/Flag_of_the_Vatican_City.svg/50px-Flag_of_the_Vatican_City.svg.png" title="WikiProjects" width="50" height="50" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/00/Flag_of_the_Vatican_City.svg/75px-Flag_of_the_Vatican_City.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/00/Flag_of_the_Vatican_City.svg/100px-Flag_of_the_Vatican_City.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="500" data-file-height="500" /></div>\n</td>\n<td style="text-align:left; padding:.3em 0">\n<center>\n<p><b><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Vatican_City" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Vatican City">Vatican City</a></b>&#160;</p>\n</center>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<table style="width:100%; background:none">\n<tr>\n<td style="width:50px">\n<div class="floatright"><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Roman_Curia" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Roman Curia"><img alt="Coat of arms Holy See.svg" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/31/Coat_of_arms_Holy_See.svg/45px-Coat_of_arms_Holy_See.svg.png" width="45" height="50" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/31/Coat_of_arms_Holy_See.svg/68px-Coat_of_arms_Holy_See.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/31/Coat_of_arms_Holy_See.svg/90px-Coat_of_arms_Holy_See.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="1160" data-file-height="1300" /></a></div>\n</td>\n<td style="text-align:left; padding:.3em 0">\n<center>\n<p><b><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Roman_Curia" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Roman Curia">Roman Curia Taskforce</a></b>&#160;</p>\n</center>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<div style="margin:-.8em 0">\n<div class="noprint" style="margin:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; padding:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; text-align:right;"></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div style="float:right; width:100%">\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid #E32636; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #FFD700; color: black; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: black"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Vatican_City/Featured_content&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: black">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:black;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Featured_content"><i>Featured content</i></span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #E32636; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: #FFFFFF;opacity: 1; color: black; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<div class="thumb tright">\n<div class="thumbinner" style="width:202px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Vatican-ChapelleSixtine-Plafond.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/12/Vatican-ChapelleSixtine-Plafond.jpg/200px-Vatican-ChapelleSixtine-Plafond.jpg" width="200" height="150" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/12/Vatican-ChapelleSixtine-Plafond.jpg/300px-Vatican-ChapelleSixtine-Plafond.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/12/Vatican-ChapelleSixtine-Plafond.jpg/400px-Vatican-ChapelleSixtine-Plafond.jpg 2x" data-file-width="3264" data-file-height="2448" /></a>\n<div class="thumbcaption">\n<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Vatican-ChapelleSixtine-Plafond.jpg" class="internal" title="\xe6\x94\xbe\xe5\xa4\xa7"></a></div>\nA post-restoration section of the ceiling of the Sistine Chapel which includes the two panels reproduced above.</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>The <b>restoration of the frescoes of the Sistine Chapel</b> was one of the most significant <a href="/wiki/Art_restoration" class="mw-redirect" title="Art restoration">art restorations</a> of the 20th century. The <a href="/wiki/Sistine_Chapel" title="Sistine Chapel">Sistine Chapel</a> was built by <a href="/wiki/Pope_Sixtus_IV" title="Pope Sixtus IV">Pope Sixtus IV</a> within the <a href="/wiki/Apostolic_Palace" title="Apostolic Palace">Vatican</a> immediately to the north of <a href="/wiki/St._Peter%27s_Basilica" title="St. Peter\'s Basilica">St. Peter\'s Basilica</a> and completed in about 1481. Its walls were decorated by a number of <a href="/wiki/Italian_Renaissance_painting" title="Italian Renaissance painting">Renaissance painters</a> who were among the most highly regarded artists of late 15th century Italy, including <a href="/wiki/Domenico_Ghirlandaio" title="Domenico Ghirlandaio">Ghirlandaio</a>, <a href="/wiki/Pietro_Perugino" title="Pietro Perugino">Perugino</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Sandro_Botticelli" title="Sandro Botticelli">Botticelli</a>. The Chapel was further enhanced under <a href="/wiki/Pope_Julius_II" title="Pope Julius II">Pope Julius II</a> by the painting of <a href="/wiki/Sistine_Chapel_ceiling" title="Sistine Chapel ceiling">the ceiling</a> by <a href="/wiki/Michelangelo" title="Michelangelo">Michelangelo</a> between 1508 and 1512 and by the painting of the <i><a href="/wiki/The_Last_Judgment_(Michelangelo)" title="The Last Judgment (Michelangelo)">Last Judgment</a></i>, commissioned by <a href="/wiki/Pope_Clement_VII" title="Pope Clement VII">Pope Clement VII</a> and completed in 1541, again by Michelangelo. The <a href="/wiki/Tapestry" title="Tapestry">tapestries</a> on the lowest tier, today best known from the <a href="/wiki/Raphael_Cartoons" title="Raphael Cartoons">Raphael Cartoons</a> (painted designs) of 1515\xe2\x80\x9316, completed the ensemble.</p>\n<p>Together the paintings make up the greatest pictorial scheme of the Renaissance. Individually, some of Michelangelo\'s paintings on the ceiling are among the most notable works of western art ever created. The <a href="/wiki/Fresco" title="Fresco">frescoes</a> of the Sistine Chapel and in particular the ceiling and accompanying <a href="/wiki/Lunette" title="Lunette">lunettes</a> by Michelangelo have been subject to a number of restorations, the most recent taking place between 1980 and 1994. This most recent restoration had a profound effect on art lovers and historians, as colours and details that had not been seen for centuries were revealed.<br />\n<a href="/wiki/Restoration_of_the_Sistine_Chapel_frescoes" title="Restoration of the Sistine Chapel frescoes"><b>Read more...</b></a></p>\n<div style="margin:-.8em 0">\n<div class="noprint" style="margin:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; padding:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; text-align:right;"></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div style="float:right; width:100%">\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid #E32636; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #FFD700; color: black; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:ri